{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:38.303002+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: f2eba89c3234fe5e1e08e09360624b73ba6212ee)", "id": "lc_c6319116-e11e-4c5f-abb7-495fd2fb4e6e"}, {"type": "text", "text": "const tokens = {\n  admin: {\n    token: 'admin-token',\n  },\n  editor: {\n    token: 'editor-token',\n  },\n}\n\nconst users = {\n  'admin-token': {\n    roles: ['admin'],\n    introduction: 'I am a super administrator',\n    avatar:\n      'https://wpimg.wallstcn.com/f778738c-e4f8-4870-b634-56703b4acafe.gif',\n    name: 'Super Admin',\n  },\n  'editor-token': {\n    roles: ['editor'],\n    introduction: 'I am an editor',\n    avatar:\n      'https://wpimg.wallstcn.com/f778738c-e4f8-4870-b634-56703b4acafe.gif',\n    name: 'Normal Editor',\n  },\n}\n\nmodule.exports = [\n  // user login\n  {\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/login',\n    type: 'post',\n    response: (config) => {\n      const { username } = config.body\n      const token = tokens[username]\n\n      // mock error\n      if (!token) {\n        return {\n          code: 60204,\n          message: 'Account and password are incorrect.',\n        }\n      }\n\n      return {\n        code: 20000,\n        data: token,\n      }\n    },\n  },\n\n  // get user info\n  {\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/info.*',\n    type: 'get',\n    response: (config) => {\n      const { token } = config.query\n      const info = users[token]\n\n      // mock error\n      if (!info) {\n        return {\n          code: 50008,\n          message: 'Login failed, unable to get user details.',\n        }\n      }\n\n      return {\n        code: 20000,\n        data: info,\n      }\n    },\n  },\n\n  // user logout\n  {\n    url: '/vue-admin-template/user/logout',\n    type: 'post',\n    response: () => {\n      return {\n        code: 20000,\n        data: 'success',\n      }\n    },\n  },\n]\n", "id": "lc_5b0663e5-3e9e-4bd1-91e9-f5522e5201d7"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "2e5d1398-58b1-4161-9ecc-18a79ea90d39", "tool_call_id": "call_3640a73ec9c34756a1727c96", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:57.014032+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a complete breakdown of how this Vue admin template handles environment switching and its mock login credentials.\n\n---\n\n## How Development vs Production API Base Paths Are Switched\n\nThe template uses a **three-layer approach** to switch between environments:\n\n### Layer 1 — Environment variable files (Vue CLI convention)\n\n| File | `ENV` | `VUE_APP_BASE_API` |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.env.development` | `'development'` | `'/dev-api'` |\n| `.env.production` | `'production'` | `'/prod-api'` |\n\nVue CLI automatically loads the matching `.env.*` file based on the command (`npm run serve` → development, `npm run build` → production), so `process.env.VUE_APP_BASE_API` is set to `/dev-api` or `/prod-api` at build time.\n\n### Layer 2 — `vue.config.js` conditional logic\n\nThe config file derives a boolean:\n```js\nconst isDev = process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'\n```\nand uses it to toggle several settings:\n\n| Setting | Development | Production |\n|---|---|---|\n| `publicPath` | `'/'` | `'/vue3-admin-template/'` |\n| `lintOnSave` | `true` | `false` |\n| `css.sourceMap` | `true` | `false` |\n| `devServer.before` (mock server) | **Loaded** via `require('./mock/mock-server.js')` | Not loaded (not wired) |\n\n### Layer 3 — Mock server (development only)\n\nIn development mode, `vue.config.js` attaches `mock/mock-server.js` as the `devServer.before` hook. That script:\n\n1. Imports all mock route modules (`mock/user.js`, `mock/table.js`).\n2. Defines a `mockXHR()` function that monkey-patches `XMLHttpRequest` via **Mock.js**.\n3. Registers each mock route with `Mock.mock(new RegExp(url), type, responseFn)`, so that any XHR matching `/vue-admin-template/user/login` (etc.) is intercepted locally — no real network call is made.\n\nIn production builds the mock server is **never wired in**, so the app hits real API endpoints at the `/prod-api` base path.\n\n---\n\n## Mock Login Usernames and Their Tokens\n\nDefined in **`mock/user.js`**:\n\n| Username | Token returned on login | User profile returned by `/user/info` |\n|---|---|---|\n| `admin` | `'admin-token'` | **Super Admin** — roles: `['admin']`, intro: *\"I am a super administrator\"* |\n| `editor` | `'editor-token'` | **Normal Editor** — roles: `['editor']`, intro: *\"I am an editor\"* |\n\n### Login flow (mock):\n\n1. `POST /vue-admin-template/user/login` with body `{ username }`.\n2. The handler looks up `username` in the `tokens` map.\n3. If found → returns `{ code: 20000, data: { token: '<token>' } }`.\n4. If not found → returns `{ code: 60204, message: 'Account and password are incorrect.' }`.\n5. On subsequent `GET /vue-admin-template/user/info?token=<token>`, the matching user profile (roles, name, avatar, introduction) is returned.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1039, "prompt_tokens": 13278, "total_tokens": 14317, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 328, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 12224, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0014064264, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0005024964, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00090393}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863218-Zx1EqpM2FnIEoi2OxueW", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b8-327f-7190-b5fb-83f2f1e58bba-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13278, "output_tokens": 1039, "total_tokens": 14317, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 12224}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 328}